text: Janelle Louise Parks (born August 1, 1962) is a retired American cyclist. Competing in the individual road race she won a silver medal at the 1986 World Championships and finished tenth at the 1984 Olympics. Parks won the national title in this event in 1987, placing second in 1983 and 1988. ==References== Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:American female cyclists Category:Olympic cyclists of the United States Category:Cyclists at the 1984 Summer Olympics Category:People from Kettering, Ohio Category:Sportspeople from Ohio
